 BOW.\nNo. 43,738\nGeorge W Stockwell. Plaiptlff. vs, Es\ntella Stockwell Defendant.\nALIAS SUMMONS\nThe State of Montana Sends Greetings\nthe Above Named Defendant\nYou are hereby summoned t\ntlie complaint l-.t this action, which is\nfiled in the office of the Clerk\nthis Court, a copy of which Is herewith\ned upon you. and to file\nswer and serve\nthe plaintiff's attorney\ndays after the service of this summons,\nexclusive of the day of service; and in\ncase of your failure to appear or am\njudgment will be taken against you bv\ndefault for the relief demanded in the\ncomplaint.\nA concise statement of plaintiff's cause\naction Is ns follows:\nThat plaintiff and defendant here\nIntermarried at Louisville. Slate of Kei\nlucky on or about the 14th day of No\nvember 1945 and ever since have been\nand now are husband and wife\nchildren were bom as Issue\nthis marriage\nThat plaintiff Is now an actual bona\nfide resident of the Stale of Montana,\nand has been such for more than\nvenr last past and Immediately preceding\nthe commencement of this action, to\nwn; the 5th day of May 1949\nThat the defendant, disregarding the\nsolemnity of her marriage\nbeen and now is guilty of Adultery, ip\nto-wlt: that in the City of Louis\nville. Slate of Kentucky, and on\nthe 3rd day of February 1948. the de\nfendant voluntarily committed\nsexual Intercourse with a man other\nthan plaintiff, which said man\nthe husband of defendant and\ntrue name is unknown to plaintiff.\nThat said act of adultery was com\nmitted without the consent, connivance,\nprocurement or previous knowledge of\nplaintiff and plaintiff has not condoned\nsaid offense, nor lived, nor a>-hablted\nwlU) defendant since becoming cognizant\nthe commission of said offense.\nThat the maiden name of defendsnt\nwas Estella Thomas.\nPlaintiff prays for an absolute divorce\nand that the Court restore defendant'*\nmaiden name to her and for all other\nand further relief as the Court may deem\nJust and equitable In the premise\