\nresenting some 200,000 members,\npreviously supported the stand taken\nby the American Federation of\nLabor.\nRING APPLIANCE CO.\nI\nSALES and SERVICE\nj Refrigerators, Washing\nI chines, Irons, Vacuum\nCleaners\nMa- j\nj 2nd and Delaware\nPh. 5326\n<~XK~X*<~X**sX-X-X~X-X-X~X\nWHEN SHOPPING FOR\nBUTTONS and THREAD SHOP\nLOWRY'S\n1863 Harrison Ave.\nACOMA LOUNGE\nButte's Finest\n33 N. Wyoming\nFor Botter Shares\nUse\nJOCKEY RAZOR BLADES\nLEGAL NOTICES\nTHE DISTRICT COURT OF THE SEC-\nOND JUDICIAL DISTRICT OF THE IN\nSI ATE OF MONTANA. IN AND FOR:\nIMF. COUNTY OF SILVER BOW\n43 7#2 I\nLucille C OLrarv. Plaint id Pliciuia No\nMcPhgil. Coum\\ Treasurer ol the County\nSilier Bov. State ol Montana Andre\u00bb\nHasoern. it a\nto\nthe\nLeo Moodv\u2014Court.\nt dead all unknown\nAndrew Haspern.\nAndrew Haspeni. if .such\nbe. Fred R Jones and wile.\nMoody, if alive; if\ndevis\nheirs and or devise\ndeceased Mrs\nperson the\nEdith S Jones; L\ndead, all unknown heirs and\nLeo Moody, deceased Mrs\nsuch person there be. all unknown\nheirs and or devisees of Peter M Car\n1er. deceased. Mrs Peter M Carter.\nsuch person there be. Carolina Thurlle.\nothe\nalive; if dead; all unknown heirs and or\ndevisees of Carolina Thurlle. otherwise\nknown a., Charlum Thurlle. and all other th\nm\u00c4\nor any thereof adverse to plaitiffs own\nership. or any cloud upon plaintiffs title\nthereto; w hether such claim or possible\nclaim be present or contingent. Including\nr i nmi nr nnvvihiP r'*im nr dower in-\na.n claim or possible c.a m or dour. i\nchoale. or accrued. Defendants.\nSUMMONS\nThe Suae of Montana Sends Greetings\nloathe to answer\ntlle comp i Bmt in mis action, which is\nllled lh e ofllcr me clerk ot this\ncourt, a copy which herewith served\nupon you, i* n( J tiu J\u2122' m\u2122pu, ntl n*\nl \"P, 5 thl n^ twenty ,20. dnv\u00ef niter\nthe service ol this summons, exclusive of\nllie day of service, and in case ol Jour\nallure b u r y0 ls by Viault for\nthe relief demanded in the comp